## Process and Team Changes

### Code coverage

The Errata Tool team continues to gradually improve code coverage by requiring
all new features and bugfixes to be accompanied by an autotest.

In Errata Tool 3.12.3 our coverage ratio is 94.1%.

[![Rcov coverage report](images/3.12.3/rcov.png)](images/3.12.3/rcov.png)

### Team changes

Rohan McGovern is leaving the team permanently to lead the newly formed
Content Delivery team, who will be responsible for improving the processes
and tools in the part of the release workflow downstream from Errata Tool.
Jason McDonald will be the Product Owner for that team, but also continues
as the Product Owner for Errata Tool.

What's Next
------------

### Errata Tool 3.12.z

The team will continue to select bugs and RFEs flagged as errata-3.12
in Bugzilla for inclusion in two week sprints. Once enough content is
verified and ready to ship we will do an end-of-sprint release. The
next release in this series will be 3.12.4.

To see current work in progress take a look at the [scrum board in
JIRA][scrumboard].

To see what's currently scheduled for ET 3.12 take a look at [bugs flagged with
errata-3.12 in Bugzilla][bugs_this] or the [Errata Tool Road Map][roadmap].

